Marketing Analyst
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 11:17:29
Ref. JB3047854
Job Description
Responsible for performing research and providing insights regarding the market, trends, competitors, potential and existing customers, and current campaigns.
Key responsibilities are but not limited to:
* Track industry information, and research competitor activities and industry trends.
* Analyze marketing metrics to identify cause and effect relationships.
* Generate reports that analyze competition and customers.
* Stay abreast of market and industry trends.
* Organize and manage cross-tactic marketing data.
* Standardize and broaden marketing metric reporting and tracking.
* Develop new ways of viewing and analyzing marketing data.
Must Have (Advanced)
statistical analysis and research methodologies, advanced computer skills
(mainly Ms Excel).
Skills
Qualifications and Skills required:
-
Minimum of a bachelor’s degree in any of the following fields: business administration, economics, marketing or statistics
-	Advanced analytical skills & enjoys dealing with numbers and seeing patterns and trends.
-	Background on market research and analytical job is an advantage but not mandatory
-	Excellent interpersonal communication skills & with pleasing personality
-	Advanced knowledge in Excel
-	Knowledge in visual basics, other spreadsheet, statistical software or CRM system are plus points but not mandatory
Education
bachelor’s degree (business administration, economics, marketing or statistics)
